Cluster Architecture

Worker Nodes
    - host applications as containers
    - handle networking between apps across the     cluster and from outside the cluster

Master 
    - manage
    - plan
    - schedule
    - monitor

ETCD Cluster
    - stores info in key data format

Kube scheduler
    - identifies right node to place container on based on resource requiremnts, rules and configurations

Controller manager
    node controller
        - nodes
        - onboarding new nodes to cluster
    replication contoller
        - required # of containers at all times

Kube API server
    - primary managemnt component
    - orchestrate all operations in cluster
    - used by external users for management
    - changes and maintenance

kube proxy service
    - ensures containers can reach other